cs.NE, cs.NI, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.CR 

The paper proposes a machine learning technique that utilizes reinforcement learning algorithms to manage flow entries in SDN-based datacenter networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) which deals with machine learning and optimization techniques. The paper also involves network infrastructure and control, which suggests the sub-categories cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The use of deep reinforcement learning also indicates the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning) as a likely category. Finally, the paper involves security and privacy concerns related to network traffic, which suggests the sub-category cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
